IPSLA TARGET UNION

TargetType

tunnel-id-target: IPSLA-TUNNEL-ID

Tunnel ID target

ipv4-pseudowire-target: IPSLA-IPV4-PW

IPv4 pseudowire target

ipv4-prefix-target: IPSLA-IPV4-PREFIX

IPv4 prefix target

  "ipv6-address-target": "string",
  "ipv4-address-target": "string",
  "target-type": "string",
  "tunnel-id-target": {
    "tunnel-id": "integer"
  },
  "ipv4-pseudowire-target": {
    "virtual-circuit-id": "integer",
    "address": "string"
  },
  "ipv4-prefix-target": {
    "mask-length": "integer",
    "address": "string"
  }
}

IPSLA-ICMP-PATH-JITTER-SPEC-STATS-BAG:

ICMP Path Jitter Statistics for a Hop

packet-loss-count: integer

Number of packets lost

jitter: integer

Jitter value for this node in the path

source-address: string

IP Address of the source

neg-jitter-count: integer

Number of negative jitter values

response-time: integer

RTT

out-of-sequence-count: integer

Number of out of sequence packets

discarded-sample-count: integer

Number of discarded samples

packet-interval: integer

Interval between echos in ms

pos-jitter-min: integer

Minimum positive jitter value

sum-response-time: integer

Sum of RTT

verify-errors-count: integer

IPSLA-APPLICATION-BAG:

IPSLA application information

inactive-entries: integer

Number of inactive entries

hw-timestamp-disabled: boolean

IPSLA HW timestamp Disabled flag

max-entries: integer

Maximum number of entries

entries-configured: integer

Number of entries configured

pending-entries: integer

Number of pending entries

operation-type: string[]
version: string

Version of the IPSLA in Version.Release .Patch-level format

configurable-probes: integer

Number of configurable probes

min-memory: integer

IPSLA low memory watermark in KB

active-entries: integer

Number of active entries

Example
{
  "inactive-entries": "integer",
  "hw-timestamp-disabled": "boolean",
  "max-entries": "integer",
  "entries-configured": "integer",
  "pending-entries": "integer",

    "string"
  ],
  "version": "string",
  "configurable-probes": "integer",
  "min-memory": "integer",
  "active-entries": "integer"
}

Number of failures due to internal error

IPSLA-OPER-STATE-BAG:

IPSLA Operation State

unexpected-control-packets: integer

Unexpected control pkts puntedfrom LPTS

start-time: integer

Last start time of the operation expressedin msec since 00:00:00 UTC, January 1, 1970

local-port: integer

Cached local port

recurring: boolean

For recurring operation configured

skipped-count: integer

Number of data collection cycles skipped

operational-state: string ipsla-oper-state-inactive, ipsla-oper-state-pending, ipsla-oper-state-active

Operational state

operation-time: integer

Start time of current instance of the operation

frequency: integer

Number of configured frequency Default 60

flags: integer

Internal flags

life-remaining: integer

Number of seconds left in current life

unexpected-packets: integer

Unexpected probe pkts punted from LPTS

attempt-count: integer

Number of data collection attempts

modification-time: integer

Last modification time of the operation expressed in msec since 00:00:00 UTC, January 1, 1970

Example
{
  "unexpected-control-packets": "integer",
  "start-time": "integer",
  "local-port": "integer",
  "recurring": "boolean",
  "skipped-count": "integer",

  "operation-time": "integer",
  "frequency": "integer",
  "flags": "integer",
  "life-remaining": "integer",
  "unexpected-packets": "integer",
  "attempt-count": "integer",

non-distributed_schema:

Statistics aggregated for the total range of values in 1-hour intervals

paths: object

Table of paths identified in the 1-hour interval

lpd-paths: object

target: IPSLA-GLOBAL-STATS-BAG

Total 1-hour aggregated statistics for the target node
